Vietnam Vets continue to have this blind sighted vision that they alone suffered the pain of the bad war. Not so, I continue to shout. DO NOT exclude us Protestors. We also have our VCR's (at least I have my 3 in the 'lock and load' position) ready for fame and frame.  Seriously, the best part of this post is to hear that this site will continue. THIS SITE WILL CONTINUE. PASS THE DISH BROTHERS AND SISTERS, WE WILL OVERCOME.  Well Done to POV, Marc, Jill, and the gang.  Keep it up! (please!).<br><br>
In my humble opinion, this site is unique in cyberspace history, as well as warfare history, and well could provide<br>
data and info for future generations wanting to see both sides of a war and hopefully teach their leaders the lesson that war need not be.  Never in the history of the USA has this been so readily believeable let alone accessible.<br><br>
&quot;get on&quot; POV, as my many patients are off to say.  And I agree. You have done the un &quot;do-able&quot; and it worked. The magic of this site is that you created the stage, and we, ALL, from all compass points on the political compass, came to dance. And we danced, like the wind of madness, we danced, (and some of us wrote lousy poetic lines) about it.<br><br>
The key is that it is. That it happened, and we all connected.  Thank you Mark and Jill, and all at POV, for the stage that gave birth to the magic. And to the healing. At the risk of sounding maudlin, I really don't think anything close to this exists, nor will it ever anywhere else. Man, (and woman), what a thing this is.  (words fail me, so I am gone)<br><br>
Doc Spatz
